# Better-call-behdad audit flow
> From /behdad to fixed, with a human approval gate

[start]    begin: User runs /behdad on a project
[process]  scope: 0 - Understand and scope
[process]  scan: 1 - Deterministic scan with real tools
[process]  inspect: 2 - Inspect (7 specialists run in parallel)
[process]  critic: 3 - Critic gate (verify findings, drop false positives)
[process]  aggregate: 4 - Aggregate (dedup, rank by risk, gate low confidence)
[process]  reports: Two reports - Full Diagnostic and Prioritized Action
[decision] approve: 5 - You approve the fixes?
[process]  remediate: 6 - Remediate (snapshot, apply, verify)
[decision] verify: Verification passes?
[process]  kept: Fix kept
[process]  rollback: Auto-rollback (reported honestly)
[process]  stop: Stop - nothing is changed
[process]  learn: 7 - Learn (remember dismissed findings)
[end]      done: Done

begin -> scope
scope -> scan
scan -> inspect
inspect -> critic
critic -> aggregate
aggregate -> reports
reports -> approve
approve -> remediate : Yes
approve -> stop : No
remediate -> verify
verify -> kept : Yes
verify -> rollback : No
kept -> learn
rollback -> learn
stop -> learn
learn -> done
